metadata.name: Hidden Intersections #66
metadata.description:
In this piece, two grids overlap:

1. a perfect one composed of lines drawn on the screen
2. an irregular one composed of linear zones that reference other parts of the screen

Everything you see in the final composition is a result of the overlapping intersections of these two grids with each other, and eventually themselves.


------------

Created as part of #genuaryTogether for #genuary2023, for the 4th day, theme: "intersections".

source code: https://github.com/protozoo/genuary23_04_intersections

controls:
- "s" key: save a png of the display
- "w" key: generate and save a 4k widescreen version of your seed (it will look different, but always be the same)

metadata.name: Lineamenta #4
metadata.description:
Outlines can be seen as a reflection of the human desire for order and structure in the world around us. Just as we use outlines to organize our thoughts and ideas, we also seek to impose order on the natural world through our scientific understanding and categorization of phenomena.

However, the act of outlining also highlights the limitations of our understanding and the subjectivity of our perspectives. An outline can never fully capture the complexity and nuance of a subject, and different individuals may have vastly different perspectives on the same topic.

In this way, outlines can be seen as both a tool for understanding and a reminder of the inherent uncertainty and subjectivity of our perceptions. It is a reminder that our understanding of the world is always evolving and that there's always more to discover.

- Press [d] to download your copy of Lineamenta.

~ Made in p5.js and chroma.js ~ by simplisto ~ December 2022

metadata.name: YAWYE #27
metadata.description:
This is YAWYE,

metadata.name: Specter of Fears #363
metadata.description:
In the dreamlike landscape of our minds, the specter of fears is like a wraith, ever-present and ethereal. It whispers in our ear, reminding us of all the things we dare not face. It is a shadow that falls across our hearts, casting a pall of doubt and uncertainty. But even as it haunts us, we must remember that it is a part of us. We must learn to accept its presence, and to use it to our advantage. For fear is not always a curse, it is a guide that shows us where we must grow stronger. It is a companion that walks with us through the dark night, illuminating the path ahead. By embracing our fears, we find the courage to face them, and to overcome them. We find the strength to live fully, to love fiercely, and to pursue our dreams with abandon.

Controls :

• Press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to make a capture and download a PNG with a resolution of x1, x2, x3 or x4.

———————

Specter of Fears by Ferdinand Dervieux, 2023

metadata.name: Atoms' Gaze #74
metadata.description:
How the lives of many affect the whole.

A holistic exploration of the growth of crystalline structures. Discovering the complexity of natural forms built from the simple rules of a deterministic system. What choice do individuals have but to be part of the story?

As microscopic particles interact and coalesce they form the macrocosm. The path they take however, is only known once it is complete. Along the way they may encounter many or none at all; each instance defining its past and future. The only knowns are that this will be the only path they take and that it'll always end.

Enjoy watching the structures form. Due to the nature of the system it may take some time to complete. Once it's fully rendered you can download a full resolution image by ***double clicking/tapping***

Features include: palette, foreground and background structures, particle rules, number of particles, colour displacement and noise.

Created on Chrome desktop 100.0 on 2022-04-16. Results on other browsers/devices may vary.

metadata.name: City Plans #8
metadata.description:
Cities can develop and expand in a variety of ways, including through natural population growth, migration, and annexation of surrounding areas. Urbanization, or the movement of people from rural areas to cities, can also contribute to a city's growth. Additionally, cities may expand through planned developments such as new housing developments, industrial parks, and transportation projects. Some cities also experience revitalization and gentrification, in which disinvested areas are rebuilt and revitalized. Factors such as economic conditions, government policies, and infrastructure can also play a role in a city's development and expansion.
"City Plans" depicts the concept of how cities develop and expand through planning and design. It emphasizes the role of city planners and architects in shaping the built environment, and the idea that a city's growth and development is guided by a master plan or blueprint.
- hit 'p' to save .png
- hit 's' to save .svg

metadata.name: GRAVITATE #28
metadata.description:
Each piece in this collection is made from the simple concept of layering grids of circles. The varying grid sizes, circle sizes, positions and colors combine to create interesting dithering effects. There are seven color palettes in the algorithm and these range from low contrast, muted palettes (e.g. Mystic Sands) to high contrast, super saturated palettes (e.g. Inferno).

- - -

GRAVITATE is my first generative art collection and was made using only p5.js.

- - -

Commands:
Press `1` to save a low-res PNG 1200x1800
Press `2` to save a high-res PNG 4800x7200

Note that it may take up to 10secs for the image render to complete.

metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #3897
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
